.\" manpage for toxic
.\" contact notadecent@tox.im to correct errors or typos
.TH toxic 1 "23 nov 2013" "Tox Project"
.SH NAME
.B toxic
\- CLI Tox client

.SH SYNOPSIS
toxic [-f | -n]

.SH DESCRIPTION
toxic is a feature-rich CLI client for toxcore

.SH OPTIONS
.B -f
filename
    Use alternate datafile "filename"
.br
.B -n
    Don't write changes to datafile

.br
.B -4
    Force an IPv4 connection

.SH USAGE
Change 
.B buffers
with [Tab]
.br
The following commands must be preceded by a slash ( 
.B/ 
)
when run outside the main buffer.
.br
.B /connect
IP PORT KEY
    Manually connect to one of the DHT servers available from <http://wiki.tox.im/Servers>
.br
.B /nick
nick
    Set nickname
.br
.B /status
.br
type message
    Set status to [ online | busy | away ] with optional message
.br
.B /note
message
    Set personal note
.br
.B /myid
    Print ID
.br
.B /add
ID message
    Add ID with optional greeting message
.br
.B /accept
n
    Accept friendrequest of specified n
.br
.B /groupchat
    Create groupchat
.br
.B /help
    Print help overview message
.br
.B /clear
    Clear buffer
.br
.B /quit, /q, /exit
    Exit toxic

.SH BUGS
Please report bugs on GitHub <https://github.com/Tox/Toxic/issues>

.SH AUTHOR
Original author: plutooo
.br
Repo maintainer: JFreegman
.br
